Class ExcelReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • ExcelReader

  • public class ExcelReader
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains static methods for parsing Room, Student, and Teacher spreadsheet files into ArrayLists of Room, Student and Teacher objects.

      • getStartTimeArr

        public static int[] getStartTimeArr(java.lang.String[] times,
                                    int dayOffset)
                             throws InvalidInputFormatException
        Given a string array of meeting times, create an integer array of start times, with each integer representing the number of minutes that have passed since 12:00 AM Monday. dayOffset represents the number of days since Monday. Monday would have a 0 dayOffset, Tuesday a 1, Wednesday a 2, etc. Date are expected to follow the following format guidelines: - Dates must be in AM/PM format, not military time - Leading 0s before single digit hours are optional, but accepted - There may be any number of spaces, or none, between the minutes and AM or PM - AM and PM may be written as am, AM, pm, or PM, but mixed capitalization is not allowed
        Parameters:
        times - an array of String times i.e 12:00 AM
        dayOffset - the offset as specified above
        Returns:
        an integer Array of converted Strings to times
        Throws:
        InvalidInputFormatException - InvalidInputFormatException

        Creates a Student object with the necessary data
        Parameters:
        id - index of the id of a Student
        fName - index of the first name of the Student
        lName - index of the last name of the Student
        a - index of the age of the Student
        g - index of the gender of the Student
        check - index of "yes" or "no", based on if the student wants the same teacher again
        rTeacher - index of name of the returning teacher
        iORStudent - index of instrument of the returning student if they are returning
        i1 - index of first choice instrument
        i2 - index of second choice instrument
        i3 - index of third choice instrument
        y1 - index of first choice instrument years of experience
        y2 - index of second choice instrument years of experience
        y3 - index of third choice instrument years of experience
        l - index of language of the preferred student, if not English
        t1 - index of times that the student is available on Monday
        t2 - index of times that the student is available on Tuesday
        t3 - index of times that the student is available on Wednesday
        t4 - index of times that the student is available on Thursday
        t5 - index of times that the student is available on Friday
        currentRow - the current XSSFRow that is being operated on in the spreadsheet
        Returns:
        a new Student object
        Throws:
        InvalidInputFormatException - InvalidInputFormatException
